text: Aline Archimbaud (born 2 November 1948) is a French politician. She is a member of the French Senate who represents the department of Seine-Saint- Denis. She is a member of the Écologistes !. She was born in Belfort. Archimbaud was elected to the European Parliament in 1992 and served until 1994 as a member of The Green Group in the European Parliament. She was elected to the French senate on 2 September 2011. == References == Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:French Senators of the Fifth Republic Category:MEPs for France 1989–1994 Category:20th-century women MEPs for France Category:Women members of the Senate (France) Category:Senators of Seine-Saint-Denis Category:Officiers of the Légion d'honneur
